Imaginary numbers are not the same as negative numbers. If you read 
somewhere on Ask Dr. Math that i represents -1, you were 
misunderstanding it; if you can tell me where that was, I'll take a 
look to see if it needs to be clarified. I assume you have read the 
FAQ on imaginary numbers:

  http://mathforum.org/dr.math/faq/faq.imag.num.html

